President Obama congratulates the people and government of Kyrgyzstan for successfully carrying out parliamentary elections. He commends the voters for participating in the historic election, demonstrating their commitment to peaceful and democratic means of selecting their government. While some flaws and irregularities were reported by election observers, the election also showcased positive attributes of a genuine democracy, such as a competitive campaign period and free monitoring by domestic and international observers. The United States has actively supported Kyrgyzstan's democratic achievement through assistance programs and participation in the election monitoring mission. President Obama emphasizes that elections are just one aspect of democratic governance and calls for the formation of a coalition government that can effectively and peacefully govern the country. Despite the challenges ahead, the successful election gives hope to supporters of democracy and reaffirms the commitment to help Kyrgyzstan consolidate their democracy, boost their economy, and maintain peace and security.